Money Stuff =0A One theme of this column is that public companies should do=
 stupid stuff to =0Amake their stocks go up. Not exclusively! They should a=
lso do a =0A=0A=0A <> =0A =0A<https://sli.bloomberg.com/click=3Fs=3D825881&=
stpe=3Ddefault&li=3D11745045&m=3D21d6dea82d6b16615cf44233be620525&p=3D11182=
024>=0A=0A=0A=0APalantir=0A=0AOne theme of this column is that public compa=
nies should do stupid stuff to =0Amake their stocks go up. Not exclusively!=
 They should also do a good job of =0Arunning a profitable business. It=E2=
=80=99s just, if the opportunity presents itself to =0Anon-fraudulently mak=
e your stock go up for stupid reasons, why not take it=3F=0A=0AI often writ=
e about this in the context of meme stocks. The paradigmatic =0Aexample is =
that Adam Aron, the chief executive officer of AMC Entertainment =0AHolding=
s Inc., did a YouTube interview in which he was apparentlynot wearing =0Apa=
nts <>. Retail investors =E2=80=94 well, some retail investors anyway =E2=
