d.=C2=A0If a bank (1) makes loans and then (2) loses money if they don=E2=
=80=99t get paid back, it will try very hard to make loans that will get pa=
id back. If a bank (1) makes loans and then (2) sells them to someone else,=
 who will lose money if they don=E2=80=99t get paid back, it will try less =
hard. It will still try! It is good for the bank=E2=80=99s long-term busine=
ss to make good loans, so it can keep selling them to willing buyers. It=E2=
=80=99s just less important for the loans to all be good, if the buyers tak=
